<p>As the pricing seems reasonable I decided to go ahead. The page is loaded over HTTPS so we start well but to my surprise the form contains a <strong>password remainder</strong> field. Password remainders areÂ a bad practice as users tend to fill them with their password (when allowed) or with a hint that is an obvious give away.<!--more--></p>

